{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Main Axis","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Glossary/Main_Axis","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The main axis in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Glossary/Flexbox\">flexbox</a> is defined by the direction set by the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/flex-direction\"><code>flex-direction</code></a> property. There are four possible values for <code>flex-direction</code>. These are:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><code>row</code></li>\n  <li><code>row-reverse</code></li>\n  <li><code>column</code></li>\n  <li><code>column-reverse</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Should you choose <code>row</code> or <code>row-reverse</code> then your main axis will run along the row in the inline direction.</p>\n<p>\n  <img src=\"/en-US/docs/Glossary/Main_Axis/basics1.png\" alt=\"In this image the flex-direction is row which forms the main axis\" width=\"522\" height=\"152\" loading=\"lazy\">\n</p>\n<p>Choose <code>column</code> or <code>column-reverse</code> and your main axis will run top to bottom of the page in the block direction.</p>\n<p>\n  <img src=\"/en-US/docs/Glossary/Main_Axis/basics2.png\" alt=\"Three flex items taking up the full width of the container, displayed one below the other in code order. Flex-direction is set to column. The main axis is vertical i.e. from top to bottom\" width=\"709\" height=\"227\" loading=\"lazy\">\n</p>\n<p>On the main axis you can control the sizing of flex items by adding any available space to the items themselves, by way of <code>flex</code> properties on the items. Or, you can control the space between and around items by using the <code>justify-content</code> property.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"property_reference","title":"Property reference","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/flex-basis\"><code>flex-basis</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/flex-direction\"><code>flex-direction</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/flex-grow\"><code>flex-grow</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/flex-shrink\"><code>flex-shrink</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/justify-content\"><code>justify-content</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/flex\"><code>flex</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"further_reading","title":"Further reading","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>CSS Flexbox Guide: <em><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Flexible_Box_Layout/Basic_Concepts_of_Flexbox\">Basic Concepts of Flexbox</a></em></li>\n  <li>CSS Flexbox Guide: <em><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Flexible_Box_Layout/Aligning_Items_in_a_Flex_Container\">Aligning items in a flex container</a></em></li>\n  <li>CSS Flexbox Guide: <em><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Flexible_Box_Layout/Controlling_Ratios_of_Flex_Items_Along_the_Main_Ax\">Controlling Ratios of flex items along the main axis</a></em></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The main axis in flexbox is defined by the direction set by the flex-direction property. There are four possible values for flex-direction. These are:","popularity":0.0005,"modified":"2022-09-21T02:09:26.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Axe principal","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Main Axis (主軸)","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"주축","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"Главная ось","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"主轴","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/glossary/main_axis","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/glossary/main_axis/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/ed947b2c608428b62a60f07d09dc543f732dc09b","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Glossary","title":